description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to support the Trust with the effective management of Fire Safety. This post will be based within the Estates &amp; Facilities Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dedicated individual with significant experience of Fire Safety to join the Trust’s Estate &amp; Facilities Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will work across Trust sites to support the Trust, Departments and Teams in meeting their statutory responsibilities and fire safety needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be an experienced Fire Safety Professional, competent in developing and delivering a range of high quality fire safety training. The post holder will be competent to provide expert and timely advice to Capital and Operational Estates Managers and teams, in relation to; fire safety precautions, legislation, HTM’s, associated guidance, British standards and building regulations. In addition the post holder will be competent at; developing policies and SOP’s and undertaking fire risk assessments. The post holder will possess a high level of communication skills and be capable of communicating effectively with employees and managers at all levels within the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to provide a friendly and professional working environment, whilst delivering a high standard of customer care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to a standard Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check. Successful candidates will either have a valid DBS check with the Trust or will be required to pay for the cost of the DBS Disclosure which is £29.50, the cost of which will be deducted from first salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthony Whittaker, Estates Officer - Engineering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;anthony.whittaker@nwbh.nhs.uk / 01925 664000&lt;/p&gt;
